  "text": "Subsequently, we tested the efficacy of 1 mg/ml AMEED to heal corneal defects in a rabbit model. The results showed that administration of AMEED every 2 hours was more effective than administration at 6-hour intervals. Previous research using in vitro wound-healing models has shown a positive dose-dependent effect of HAM suspensions on corneal re-epithelialization [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
